<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Container version="2">
  <Name>Apache-Reverse-Proxy</Name>
  <Repository>auskento/apache-reverse-proxy:latest</Repository>
  <Registry>https://hub.docker.com/</Registry>
  <Network>bridge</Network>
  <MyIP/>
  <Shell>bash</Shell>
  <Privileged>false</Privileged>
  <Support>https://github.com/auskento/apache-reverse-proxy</Support>
  <Project>https://github.com/auskento/apache-reverse-proxy</Project>
  <Category>Network:Web</Category>
  <TemplateURL>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/auskento/apache-reverse-proxy/main/apache-reverse-proxy.xml</TemplateURL>
  <Icon>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/auskento/apache-reverse-proxy/main/apache-reverse-proxy-150.png</Icon>
  <PostArgs/>
  <CloudSync>false</CloudSync>
  <Description>Apache Reverse Proxy with flexible deployment modes, 14 media services, customizable dashboards (4 styles), and authentication options (None, Basic, Entra ID, Google OAuth).</Description>
  <Overview>Apache Reverse Proxy for Media Services&#13;&#13;This container provides:&#13;- Public mode: Automatic HTTPS with Let's Encrypt SSL certificates&#13;- Private mode: Internal-only deployment without certificate generation&#13;- Reverse proxy for up to 16 different services&#13;- Responsive web dashboard with 4 customizable styles: classic, modern, sleek, minimal&#13;- Dashboard customization: custom title, icon, and default landing page&#13;- Four authentication options: None, Basic Auth, Entra ID (Microsoft), or Google OAuth2&#13;- Custom service icons and smart icon management&#13;- Service health monitoring&#13;&#13;Quick Start (Public Deployment - ACCESS_MODE=public):&#13;1. Set DOMAIN and EMAIL (required for Let's Encrypt)&#13;2. Choose AUTHTYPE (none, basic, entra, or google)&#13;3. Enable services and configure backend URLs&#13;4. (Optional) Customize dashboard STYLE, DASHBOARD_NAME, DASHBOARD_ICON, LANDING&#13;&#13;Quick Start (Private Deployment - ACCESS_MODE=private):&#13;1. Set ACCESS_MODE=private&#13;2. Choose AUTHTYPE (none or basic only - Entra/Google not available)&#13;3. Enable services and configure backend URLs&#13;4. DOMAIN and EMAIL still required in config but not used for certificates&#13;&#13;Supported Services (16):&#13;SABnzbd, NZBGet, NZBHydra, Deluge, Transmission, qBittorrent, Radarr, Sonarr, Whisparr, Prowlarr, Seerr, Lidarr, Emby, Plex, Jellyfin, Tautulli&#13;&#13;Dashboard Styles:&#13;- Classic: Traditional sidebar menu&#13;- Modern: React-based with full features (recommended)&#13;- Sleek: Compact sidebar with gradient styling&#13;- Minimal: Single-column minimal design&#13;&#13;Documentation:&#13;https://github.com/auskento/apache-reverse-proxy</Overview>
  <Networking>
    <Mode>br0</Mode>
    <Publish>
      <Port>
        <HostPort>80</HostPort>
        <ContainerPort>80</ContainerPort>
        <Protocol>tcp</Protocol>
        <Description>HTTP</Description>
        <Access>External</Access>
      </Port>
      <Port>
        <HostPort>443</HostPort>
        <ContainerPort>443</ContainerPort>
        <Protocol>tcp</Protocol>
        <Description>HTTPS</Description>
        <Access>External</Access>
      </Port>
    </Publish>
  </Networking>
  <Data>
    <Volume>
      <HostDir>/mnt/user/appdata/apache-reverse-proxy/letsencrypt</HostDir>
      <ContainerDir>/etc/letsencrypt</ContainerDir>
      <Mode>rw</Mode>
      <Description>SSL Certificates</Description>
      <Access>rw</Access>
      <Exclude/>
      <IsFileShare>false</IsFileShare>
    </Volume>
    <Volume>
      <HostDir>/mnt/user/appdata/apache-reverse-proxy/logs</HostDir>
      <ContainerDir>/var/log/apache2</ContainerDir>
      <Mode>rw</Mode>
      <Description>Apache Logs</Description>
      <Access>rw</Access>
      <Exclude/>
      <IsFileShare>false</IsFileShare>
    </Volume>
  </Data>
  
